SCRAPIE, SHEEP - JAPAN (02): OIE
************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>

Date: 29 Sep 2003
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Office International des Epizooties(OIE), Disease Information [edited]

Scrapie in Japan
(Date of previous outbreak of scrapie in Japan reported to the OIE: October
2001).
Emergency report
Information received on 24 and 26 Sep 2003 from Dr Masako Kurimoto,
Director of Animal Health and Animal Products Safety Division, Ministry of
Agriculture, Forestry and Fisheries, Tokyo:
Report date: 24 Sep 2003.
Nature of diagnosis: laboratory.
Date of confirmation of diagnosis: 20 Sep 2003.
Outbreak
Location: Nakagawa district, Hokkaido Prefecture
No. of outbreaks 1
Description of affected population: a 3-year-old Suffolk ewe on a farm in
Hokkaido Prefecture.
Total number of animals in the outbreak:
species / susceptible / cases / deaths / destroyed / slaughtered
ovi / 86 / 1 / 0 / 1 / 0

Diagnosis:
A. Laboratory where diagnosis was made: National Institute of Animal
Health, Tsukuba, Ibaraki Prefecture.
B. Diagnostic tests used: western blot analysis and immunohistochemical
examination of a brain sample from the ewe.
Epidemiology:
A. Source of agent / origin of infection: unknown.
B. Other epidemiological details: since the first case in 1984, scrapie has
been reported in 32 farms with 60 positive cases including the case
diagnosed this time.
Control measures:
- The ewe was destroyed immediately after the diagnosis.
- Identification and isolation of cohort animals.
- The farm where the case of scrapie was found has been placed under
movement control by Tokachi Livestock Hygiene Service Center.
- Disinfection of the infected premises.
- Epidemiological investigation of the feed used on the farm as a possible
source of infection
